{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17640486","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17640486"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:18:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:18:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17832"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17832","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17832"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.14,0,0.66,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10546"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75737"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10546","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10546"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17832"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61250"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5728"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24590"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25028"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75737","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75737"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with chest pain. After initial assessment and electrocardiogram, she decides she wants to leave the hospital before further investigations can be completed. She demonstrates clear understanding of the situation and potential risks.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial response by the treating doctor?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document capacity assessment and contact next of kin","Complete discharge summary and arrange follow-up","Request urgent psychiatric assessment","Explain risks and document the discussion","Obtain written refusal of treatment only"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eexplain risks and document the discussion\u003C/strong\u003E. When a patient with decision-making capacity chooses to leave against medical advice, healthcare providers must respect their autonomy while ensuring they are fully informed of the risks and alternatives.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument capacity assessment and contact next of kin\u003C/strong\u003E - Contacting next of kin without the patient\u0027s consent would breach confidentiality and patient privacy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplete discharge summary and arrange follow-up\u003C/strong\u003E - This approach fails to address the immediate need to ensure informed decision-making through risk discussion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest urgent psychiatric assessment\u003C/strong\u003E - A psychiatric assessment is not indicated when a patient demonstrates clear capacity to make decisions about their care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtain written refusal of treatment only\u003C/strong\u003E - Simply obtaining written refusal without explaining risks does not meet the requirements for informed decision-making.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDocumentation should include capacity assessment, risks discussed, alternatives offered, and follow-up arrangements made. The patient should be encouraged to return if symptoms worsen and provided with appropriate discharge instructions and medications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Patients with decision-making capacity have the right to refuse medical treatment even if this may result in harm.","Healthcare providers must document capacity assessment and risks discussed when patients leave against medical advice.","Patients must be informed of risks, alternatives, and follow-up options when choosing to leave against medical advice."],"references":["Tr\u00e9panier G, Lagu\u00eb G, Dorimain MV. A step-by-step approach to patients leaving against medical advice (AMA) in the emergency department. CJEM. 2023 Jan;25(1):31-42. doi: 10.1007/s43678-022-00385-y. Epub 2022 Oct 31. PMID: 36315346; PMCID: PMC9628312.","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61250"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17832"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61250","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61250"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T12:09:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T12:09:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10546"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75737"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":nul